his%20multinational%20conglomerate%20holding%20company%2C%20from%20a%20failing%20textile%20mill%20into%20a%20%241%20trillion%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20coming%20ascension%20of%20Abel%2C%20the%20chairperson%20of%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20Energy%2C%20to%20replace%20Buffett%20is%20a%20reminder%20that%20getting%20a%20big%20promotion%20often%20involves%20a%20good%20deal%20of%20spadework.%20Once%20you%20get%20the%20gig%2C%20there%20are%20important%20things%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20as%20you%20step%20into%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20asked%20corporate%20observers%20for%20their%20advice%20on%20pathways%20to%20getting%20promoted%20and%20succeeding%20when%20you%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222cc6c687-5432-49ef-89d8-d5682bdba6b6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFind%20your%20mentors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20hoping%20to%20move%20up%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20find%20senior%20leaders%20to%20guide%20you%2C%20Andy%20Lopata%2C%20coauthor%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Financial%20Times%20Guide%20to%20Mentoring%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20might%20include%20a%20boss%20whose%20job%20you%20hope%20to%20one%20day%20land%20and%20other%20mentors%20who%20can%20be%20objective%20in%20guiding%20you%20as%20you%20forge%20key%20relationships%20and%20plan%20your%20next%20steps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStewart%20Friedman%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%20%3Cspan%3Eand%20emeritus%20professor%3C%2Fspan%3E%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania's%20Wharton%20School%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20email%20that%20when%20he%20interviews%20job%20candidates%2C%20he'll%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20will%20your%20experience%20working%20with%20me%20contribute%20to%20your%20development%20towards%20your%20most%20important%20goals%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20important%20consideration%2C%20Friedman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20your%20boss%20isn't%20thinking%20this%20way%2C%20then%20they%20are%20not%20priming%20you%20for%20taking%20the%20steps%20you%20need%20to%20prepare%20for%20your%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aaa6e2b3-d4ba-4f86-8336-8365a489c869%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELook%20for%20signs%20of%20confidence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELong%20before%20getting%20good%20news%20about%20the%20role%20you've%20been%20shooting%20for%2C%20you'll%20likely%20need%20to%20put%20in%20hard%20work%20and%20look%20for%20signs%20that%20your%20boss%20is%20confident%20that%20you'll%20succeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20indication%20you%20might%20be%20set%20to%20climb%20is%20if%20your%20boss%20trusts%20you%20with%20%26quot%3Bhigh-stakes%20decisions%26quot%3B%20and%20not%20just%20easy%20wins%2C%20Deborah%20Grayson%20Riegel%2C%20who%20teaches%20leadership%20communication%20at%20Wharton%20and%20Columbia%20Business%20School%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20boss%20asks%20you%20to%20stand%20in%20for%20them%20in%20key%20situations%20where%20%26quot%3Bthe%20stakes%20(and%20titles)%20are%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Cspan%3Eit%20can%20be%20a%20sign%20they're%20testing%20and%20showcasing%20your%20executive%20presence%20and%20credibility%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eshe%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERiegel%20said%20not%20all%20parts%20of%20moving%20up%20will%20necessarily%20be%20frictionless.%20A%20boss%20who%20views%20you%20as%20heir%20apparent%20might%20also%20offer%20candid%20feedback%2C%20even%20when%20it's%20uncomfortable.%20That%20person%20might%20also%20give%20you%20autonomy%20to%20lead%20and%20then%20support%20you%20when%20you%20stumble%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20you%20will%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20kind%20of%20trust%20signals%20they're%20preparing%20you%20for%20more%20than%20your%20current%20role%3B%20they're%20preparing%20you%20for%20theirs%2C%26quot%3B%20Riegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216793be2-2d69-4c49-8853-7b250b1cc15d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you%20get%20the%20job%2C%20don't%20just%20mimic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20lucky%20enough%20to%20get%20the%20job%20and%20will%20soon%20take%20over%2C%20it%20can%20be%20important%20to%20honor%20your%20boss's%20legacy%20without%20mimicking%20it.%20That's%20the%20case%20for%20Abel%2C%20Herminia%20Ibarra%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20London%20Business%20School%2C%20told%20BI%20via%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20wants%20a%20replica%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Buffett%20led%20through%20%26quot%3Bextreme%20delegation%2C%26quot%3B%20Ibarra%20said%2C%20Abel%20is%20often%20more%20hands-on.%20She%20said%20he'll%20need%20to%20use%20his%20instincts%20to%20make%20%26quot%3Bbold%2C%20well-judged%26quot%3B%20moves%20even%20while%20maintaining%20the%20company's%20decentralized%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20successor%20is%20always%20chosen%20for%20a%20reason%3B%20Abel%20must%20understand%20why%20he%20won%20the%20succession%20contest%20and%20lead%20from%20that%20strength%2C%26quot%3B%20Ibarra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222fc29709-cd5e-4de1-a201-5ed0d0da8307%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKeep%20some%20things%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlisa%20Cohn%2C%20an%20executive%20coach%2C%20likewise%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20stake%20out%20your%20own%20position%20and%20not%20pretend%20you're%20the%20old%20boss.%20That%20includes%20not%20promising%20things%20will%20stay%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20she%20said%2C%20it%20can%20help%20to%20hold%20onto%20some%20aspects%20of%20leadership%20that%20are%20popular%20or%20have%20worked%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Abel's%20case%2C%20that%20includes%20Buffett's%20annual%20shareholder%20meeting%2C%20which%20has%20for%20years%20been%20a%20big%20event%20for%20investors%20well%20beyond%20the%20company%2C%20Cohn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226867ac86-29bc-4104-8ee3-5a835cbc6dfc%5C%22%3EKeep%20your%20colleagues'%20success%20in%20mind%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20like%20Abel%2C%2062%2C%20and%20you've%20been%20a%20longtime%20employee%20at%20a%20company%2C%20you've%20likely%20built%20up%20many%20relationships%20with%20coworkers.%20Moving%20up%20the%20ladder%20can%20change%20some%20of%20those%20dynamics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20that%2C%20Cohn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERising%20to%20the%20position%20where%20you're%20in%20charge%20can%20lead%20to%20jealous%20coworkers%2C%20she%20said.%20If%20you're%20the%20one%20moving%20up%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20let%20your%20one-time%20peers%20know%20that%20their%20success%20remains%20important%20to%20you%2C%20Cohn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShow%20them%20early%20that%20you%20have%20their%20backs%20and%20want%20to%20support%20them%20and%20help%20them%20succeed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22411a86d4-f9ad-43d8-89df-cf5792bb7356%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20your%20mark%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECohn%20said%20one%20way%20you%20can%20establish%20yourself%20is%20by%20demonstrating%20you%20have%20strong%20judgment.%20For%20Abel%2C%20that%20could%20include%20big%20decisions%20on%20large%20investments%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20successful%2C%20high-profile%20acquisition%20or%20investment%20soon%20after%20his%20takeover%20would%20%26quot%3Breassure%26quot%3B%20investors%20and%20others%20that%20Berkshire's%20historic%20investment%20discipline%20remains%20intact%2C%20Cohn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20Abel%20should%20continue%20to%20differentiate%20himself%20by%20ensuring%20the%20business%20managers%20are%20acting%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20collective%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20taking%20action%20if%20they%20aren't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhitney%20Johnson%2C%20a%20leadership%20advisor%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20email%20that%20leadership%20transitions%20can%20spread%20fear%20because%20of%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCalm%20the%20lizard%20brain%20by%20communicating%20relentlessl