had%20just%20happened.%20It%20felt%20surreal%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20joined%20Meta%20in%20early%202024%20and%20earned%20a%20mid-year%20review%20of%20%26quot%3BAt%20or%20Above%20Expectations.%26quot%3B%20Initially%20rated%20%26quot%3BMeets%20All%20Expectations%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20January%202025%20year-end%20review%2C%20she%20was%20downgraded%20to%20%26quot%3BMeets%20Most%20Expectations%26quot%3B%20after%20a%20second%20round%20of%20director-level%20reviews.%20She%20said%20she%20suspects%20%26quot%3Bdirectors%20were%20under%20pressure%20to%20hit%20a%20layoff%20quota.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20layoff%2C%20she%20was%20dissatisfied%20with%20her%20manager%20and%20sought%20a%20transfer%20to%20a%20top-tier%20team.%20It%20was%20approved%2C%20but%20she%20was%20told%20the%20move%20could%20lower%20her%20rating%2C%20so%20she%20waited%20%E2%80%94%20only%20to%20be%20pink-slipped.%20She%20said%20she's%20not%20taking%20the%20recruiter%20up%20on%20her%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20she's%20confident%20she%20can%20land%20or%20create%20her%20next%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'll%20be%20fine.%20I%20can%20get%20another%20job%20or%20start%20something%20of%20my%20own.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22250c57f8-42a5-4b2e-b3a3-1a5e6009d57e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECut%20after%20a%20leave%20for%20burnout%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20software%20engineer%20who%20joined%20Meta%20in%20May%202024%20to%20work%20on%20cross-platform%20content%20sharing%20said%20a%20promising%20start%20unraveled%20due%20to%20internal%20politics%20over%20a%20new%20feature%20he%20prototyped.%20He%20said%20he%20took%20a%20four-month%20leave%20for%20burnout%20in%20August%20and%20returned%20in%20December%20to%20complete%20two%20more%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20weeks%20before%20the%20layoffs%2C%20he%20said%2C%20his%20new%20manager%20told%20the%20team%20everyone%20was%20%26quot%3Bsafe.%26quot%3B%20Then%20came%20the%20termination%20email%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20performance%20rating%20of%20%26quot%3BMeets%20Some%20Expectations%2C%26quot%3B%20low%20on%20Meta's%20end-of-year%20rating%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20could%20they%20evaluate%20my%20performance%20when%20I'd%20only%20worked%2010%20weeks%20in%202024%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20an%20HR%20director%20had%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Btoo%20new%20to%20evaluate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20he's%20now%20fielding%20interest%20from%20other%20companies%20and%20expects%20to%20receive%2016%20weeks%20of%20severance%2C%20he%20still%20feels%20the%20sting%20of%20his%20rating.%20%26quot%3BThe%20harmful%20'low%20performer'%20label%20still%20feels%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9c7e5ea-b2a6-49f0-90f1-b41064201f5b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20changed%20when%20I%20moved%20to%20Reality%20Labs%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20product%20manager%20joined%20Facebook%20as%20a%20contractor%20in%202018%2C%20converted%20to%20full-time%20in%202020%2C%20and%20consistently%20received%20year-end%20%26quot%3BGreatly%20Exceeds%20Expectations%26quot%3B%20ratings%20label.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20when%20she%20moved%20to%20Reality%20Labs%2C%20%26quot%3Beverything%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20manager%20would%20call%20late%20at%20night%20to%20question%20my%20capabilities%20and%20create%20doubt%2C%20even%20though%20teammates%20gave%20me%20positive%20feedback%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20review%20in%20early%202024%20dropped%20her%20two%20tiers%20to%20%26quot%3BMeets%20All%20Expectations.%26quot%3B%20Feedback%20included%20accusations%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bblinded%26quot%3B%20by%20a%20%26quot%3Bdesire%20for%20promotion%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20In%20August%202024%2C%20she%20took%20a%2012-week%20disability%20leave%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20I%20was%20physically%20ill%20from%20all%20the%20stress.%26quot%3B%20She%20returned%20in%20November%20and%20was%20laid%20off%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20being%20%26quot%3Bselective%26quot%3B%20in%20her%20hunt%20for%20a%20new%20job.%20%26quot%3BThe%20experience%20damaged%20my%20health%2C%20affected%20my%20family%2C%20and%20forced%20me%20onto%20medication%20for%20anxiety.%20I%20need%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20toxicity%20at%20the%20first%20sign%2C%20not%20wait%20until%20it%20affects%20my%20health%20and%20family%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239f5c54a-8ee5-4be2-839a-8ad8707ff6b6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20templated%20response%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20technical%20program%20manager%20was%20laid%20off%20after%20seven%20years%20of%20good%20performance%20ratings%20at%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20reorganization%20placed%20her%20under%20a%20new%20manager%20a%20few%20months%20earlier%20%E2%80%94%20a%20shift%20she%20felt%20exposed%20her.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20managers%20have%20to%20meet%20quotas%20and%20choose%20someone%20to%20cut%2C%20people%20with%20less%20history%20on%20the%20team%20are%20at%20higher%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20contacted%20my%20manager%20in%20shock%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20termination%20notice%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20wanted%20five%20minutes%20to%20talk%20to%20ensure%20I%20wasn't%20going%20crazy.%26quot%3B%20The%20manager%20responded%20with%20a%20templated%20email%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20company-approved%20language%20she%20had%20been%20required%20to%20use%20the%20day%20before%20when%20laying%20off%20her%20own%20direct%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20still%20doesn't%20know%20exactly%20what%20led%20to%20their%20selection.%20%26quot%3BWas%20it%20because%20I%20had%20significant%20equity%20vested%20when%20the%20stock%20price%20was%20low%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3B%20Was%20it%20because%20I%20expressed%20disappointment%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-rolls-back-dei-programs-202