-musk-waymo-diss-john-krafcik-robotaxi-wars-cybercab-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%20Tesla%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20being%20all%20talk%20and%20no%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20Tesla%20hopes%20to%20compete%20with%20Waymo%20someday%2C%20they've%20failed%20utterly%20and%20completely%20at%20this%20for%20each%20of%20the%2010%20years%20they've%20been%20talking%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-robotaxi-launch-austin-june-internal-details-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETesla's%20Austin%20launch%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20mark%20a%20crucial%20chapter%20in%20a%20yearslong%20debate%20over%20the%20best%20self-driving%20training%20methods%20and%20whether%20success%20will%20come%20from%20Tesla's%20big%20swings%20or%20Waymo's%20gradual%20deployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20look%20at%20how%20Tesla%20and%20Waymo%20compare%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20autonomous%20driving%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FNT6dE%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%C2%A0Tesla%20v.%20Waymo%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22723%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20A%20Waymo%20spokesperson%20referred%20BI%20to%20previous%20blog%20posts%20on%20the%20company's%20early%20rides%20and%20continued%20testing%20in%20cities%20across%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c962efa8-4cdc-407f-af73-87f787fa00dd%5C%22%3ETraining%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20and%20Waymo%20have%20taken%20radically%20different%20approaches%20to%20training%20their%20AI%20systems%20for%20self-driving.%20Tesla%20has%20relied%20on%20a%20vision-based%20approach%20that%20uses%20a%20suite%20of%20eight%20cameras%20and%20minimal%20reliance%20on%20external%20sensors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20said%20that%20Tesla%20began%20removing%20lidar%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esensors%20from%20its%20test%20vehicles%20in%202021%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecalling%20the%20technology%20an%20expensive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspac-elon-musk-lidar-luminar-velodyne-ouster-innoviz-aeva-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bcrutch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20carmaker%20has%20a%20lidar-%20and%20radar-equipped%20vehicle%20called%20the%20Ground%20Truth%20Machine%20that%20it%20uses%20for%20training%20purposes%2C%20but%20only%20for%20edge%20cases%20of%20rare%20or%20unusual%20driving%20scenarios%2C%20BI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-self-driving-software-test-drivers-project-rodeo-experiences-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo's%20Jaguar%20I-PACE%20robotaxis%20are%20outfitted%20with%20five%20lidar%20sensors%2C%20six%20radars%2C%20and%2029%20cameras%20that%20help%20its%20AI%20software%20navigate%20its%20environment%2C%20a%20company%20spokesperson%20said.%20The%20company%20says%20its%20next-generation%20Waymo%20Driver%20will%20have%20a%20reduced%20and%20cheaper%20sensor%20suite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Waymo%20robotaxis%20are%20deployed%20for%20public%20rides%2C%20Waymo%20uses%20safety%20drivers%20to%20map%20out%20a%20city%20like%20San%20Francisco%20or%20Tokyo%2C%20creating%20highly%20detailed%20maps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c90086b-3e5e-490b-8d41-b1534737ff36%5C%22%3EAutonomy%20level%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Society%20of%20Automotive%20Engineers%20(SAE)%20ranks%20self-driving%20vehicles%20on%20a%20scale%20from%20zero%20to%20five%20%E2%80%94%20five%20being%20the%20holy%20grail%20of%20autonomous%20driving%20in%20which%20a%20driverless%20vehicle%20can%20go%20anywhere%20under%20any%20environmental%20conditions%2C%20according%20to%20SAE.%20Tesla%20has%20said%20it%20operates%20as%20a%20Level%202%20vehicle%2C%20meaning%20that%20it%20operates%20as%20a%20driver-assist%20software%20with%20a%20human%20driver%20still%20behind%20the%20wheel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California%2C%20where%20Tesla%20does%20much%20of%20its%20in-house%20testing%2C%20the%20carmaker%20is%20required%20to%20secure%20a%20permit%20for%20Level%203%20and%20above%20testing.%20Tesla%20has%20not%20reported%20using%20the%20permit%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20self-driving%20software%20to%20operate%20with%20a%20safety%20driver%20but%20even%20more%20autonomy%2C%20since%202019.%20The%20company%20told%20the%20California%20DMV%20in%20December%20that%20it%20was%20currently%20operating%20as%20a%20Level%202%20vehicle%20in%20the%20state%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-autonomous-driving-california-robotaxi-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edocuments%20viewed%20by%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%2C%20along%20with%20Zoox%20and%20Nuro%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20companies%20that%20has%20deployed%20Level%204%20autonomous%20driving%20in%20the%20real%20world%2C%20which%20means%20the%20vehicle%20does%20not%20require%20a%20driver%20behind%20the%20wheel%20and%20is%20fully%20autonomous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%20robotaxis%20have%20limitations.%20The%20vehicles%20cannot%20travel%20beyond%20areas%20programmed%20into%20their%20system%2C%20and%20the%20company%20hasn't%20yet%20offered%20robotaxi%20service%20in%20cities%20that%20experience%20more%20extreme%20weather%2C%20such%20as%20snow.%20A%20Waymo%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20has%20invested%20in%20weather%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d6c70b1-e777-4858-b4a7-f6c53755dadc%5C%22%3EBusiness%20models%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20a%20more%20consumer-focused%20business%20model.%20The%20company%20sells%20beta%20versions%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-fsd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFull%20Self-Driving%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%248%2C000%2C%20or%20%2499%20a%20month.%20The%20software%20requires%20a%20licensed%20driver%20to%20supervise%20the%20vehicle%2C%20but%20it%20can%20switch%20lanes%2C%20recognize%20stop%20lights%2C%20and%20enter%20and%20exit%20highways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20company%20is%20also%20working%20on%20building%20up%20a%20commercial%20robotaxi%20fleet%2C%20Musk%20has%20said%20Tesla%20owners%20will%20one%20day%20be%20able%20to%20rent%20out%20their%20cars%20as%20a%20self-driving%20service%2C%20akin%20to%20Uber%20or%20Airbnb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo's%20business%20is%20primarily%20focused%20on%20delivering%20an%20autonomous%20rideshare%20service%20through%20Waymo%20One%20or%20through%20its%20partnership%20with%20rideshare%20platforms%20such%20as%20Uber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Tesla%2C%20Waymo%20does%20not%20manufacture%20cars%20in-house%20and%20instead%20relies%20on%20partnerships%20with%20OEMs%20to%20build%20out%20its%20robotaxi%20fleet%2C%20partnering%20with%20Jaguar%2C%20Chrysler%2C%20Hyundai%2C%20and%20Toyota.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%20has%20signaled%20interest%20in%20bringing%20its%20autonomous%20technology%20to%20personally%20owned%20vehicles.%20On%20April%2029%2C%20Waymo%20revealed%20that%20it%20was%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwaymo-early-talks-toyota-partnership-autonomous-driving-personally-owned-cars-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly%20talks%20with%20Toyota%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20explore%20bringing%20autonomy%20to%20consumer%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2256bf5f0a-6c69-4799-84f3-4871a45c852c%5C%22%3EGeographic%20deployment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20said%20it%20aims%20to%20roll%20out%20the%20service%20in%20Austin%20in%20June%20and%20in%20other%20US%20cities%20within%20the%20year.%20The%20company%20is%20still%20getting%20regulatory%20approval%20in%20California%2C%20but%20has%20several%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-robotaxi-launch-austin-june-internal-details-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein-house%20test%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20operating%20in%20cities%20across%20the%20country%2C%20including%20Phoenix%2C%20Dallas%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20Miami.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20carmaker's%20earnings%20call%20in%20April%2C%20Musk%20said%20that%20Tesla%20owners%20would%20be%20able%20to%20drive%20their%20vehicles%20autonomously%20within%20the%20year.%20Musk%20has%20said%20that%20Tesla%20will%20eventually%20deploy%20its%20services%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%20has%20chosen%20to%20gradually%20roll%20out%20its%20service%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20select%20cities.%20As%20of%20April%2C%20Waymo's%20robotaxis%20are%20offering%20fully%20driverless%20rides%20to%20the%20public%20in%20limited%20parts%20of%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area%2C%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20Phoenix%2C%20and%20Austin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20currently%20testing%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20Miami%2C%20San%20Diego%2C%20and%20Tokyo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c5d5da0-4870-4dc7-92ed-aebde933153c%5C%22%3EMiles%20driven%20autonomously%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20difficult%20to%20compare%20Tesla%20and%20Waymo's%20mileage%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20not%20released%20any%20information%20on%20how%20often%20humans%20need%20to%20take%20control%20of%20its%20self-driving%20systems%20or%20how%20many%20miles%20its%20cars%20have%20driven%20without%20intervention.%20In%20its%20most%20recent%20earnings%20report%2C%20the%20company%20said%20users%20of%20its%20beta%20FSD%20software%20have%20driven%20a%20cumulative%203.6%20billion%20miles.%20The%20company%20also%20released%20an%20update%20in%20April%20that%20Tesla%20engineers%20had%20driven%20about%2015%2C000%20miles%20using%20an%20internal%20version%20of%20its%20robotaxi%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%20has%20said%20that%20its%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erobotaxis%20have%20traveled%2056.7%20million%20miles%20as%20of%20January%2C%20miles%20driven%20without%20human%20supervision.%20The%20company%20said%20it%20provides%20over%20250%2C000%20rides%20a%20week%20as%20of%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bbc92b2c-9c42-4883-8a22-50501e2cf8a0%5C%22%3ECost%20of%20a%20robotaxi%20ride%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20not%20said%20how%20much%20the%20service%20will%20cost%2C%20but%20has%20said%20the%20price%20will%20be%20comparable%20to%20booking%20an%20Uber.%20Right%20now%2C%20Tesla%20owners%20pay%20a%20%248%2C000%20flat%20fee%20or%20%2499%20a%20month%20to%20use%20the%20beta%20version%20of%20FSD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%2C%20Waymo's%20price%20can%20vary%20depending%20on%20the%20city%20and%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20study%20conducted%20last%20year%20by%20Evercore%20ISI%20of%201%2C000%20trips%20offered%20by%20Waymo%2C%20Uber%2C%20and%20Lyft%20found%20that%20Waymo's%20price%20point%20had%20essentially%20reached%20parity%20with%20existing%20rideshare%20platforms%20by%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Waymo%20was%20more%20expensive%20at%20about%20%2424%20per%20ride%20in%20mid-2024%2C%20Waymo's%20average%20fare%20dropped%20nearly%2010%25%20to%20around%20%2422%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20brought%20Waymo%20in%20line%20with%20traditional%20rideshare%20options%2C%20with%20UberX%20at%20about%20%2421%20and%20Lyft%20at%20roughly%20%2422%20during%20the%20same%20period.%20The%20analysts%20noted%20that%20the%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20prices%20didn't%20include%20driver%20tips%2C%20unlike%20the%20all-inclusive%20Waymo%20fare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-waymo-robotaxi-comparison-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746520982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6814f4a8c6ad288d147fdc99%3